annotation protocol for ted-mdb.1971.xlsx 
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

Uncertainties and problems


! - Sentence-level broken, see: https://github.com/acoli-repo/AURIS/issues/25


- Demonstrative pronouns are often pre-annotated, although not syntactical head; e.g. 89, 174 etc.

- NP after possessive pronouns not marked by the parser, e.g. 71, 551, 568, 638 etc.

- 292: "ankle" prosthesis unclear; interpreted as prosthesis in general

- Subsets of e.g. prostheses: "uniform" or "customized" each annotated as REF=NEW entity, as long as no specific new REF-category has been created
	see: https://github.com/acoli-repo/AURIS/issues/24